The paper deals with the Nonnegative Matrix Factorization (NMF) problem, which is a well-studied problem in machine learning and data analysis. The paper discusses the complexity of the problem and provides polynomial-time algorithms for solving it under certain conditions. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and communication complexity (cs.CC) in its analysis, which are also likely sub-categories.
